Practical 4

Step 1 
How To Install SSH Server :- sudo apt-get install openssh-server

Step 2 
Enable ssh service :- sudo sysytemctl start ssh

Step 3
Test It By Login Into System Using Command :- ssh kali@power9-bmc

Step 4
Update And Then Install OpenSSH server :- Command :- sudo apt update
                                          Command :- sudo apt upgrade

Step 5
Install OpenSSH Server :- sudo apt install openssh-server

Step 6
Verify And Run SSh Service :- sudo systemctl status ssh

Step 7 :
Configure Firewall And Open Port 22 :- Command :- sudo ufw allow ssh
                                      Command :- sudo ufw enable
                                      Command :- sudo ufw status
                                      Command :- ssh 127.0.0.1
                                      
